---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Breadcrumbs from "../components/Breadcrumbs.astro";
import { SITE, authors } from "../lib/blog-data.js";
---
<BaseLayout
  title={`About - ${SITE.name}`}
  description="Sauté Sundays is Toronto's cookbook club. Every month, members cook a dish at home from the same featured cookbook, then come together at one table to share it."
  canonical="/about"
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 py-12">
    <Breadcrumbs items={[{ label: "Home", to: "/" }, { label: "About" }]} />
    <header class="mt-6">
      <div class="text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-primary">About</div>
      <h1 class="mt-2 font-serif text-5xl font-semibold leading-[1.05]">
        Toronto's cookbook club, where everyone cooks and everyone shares.
      </h1>
    </header>
    <div class="prose-article mt-10">
      <p>
        Sauté Sundays is a free, monthly potluck cookbook club based in Toronto. Every month, everyone in the group cooks a dish at home from the same featured cookbook, then brings it to share at one table. Nobody teaches. Nobody performs. Everyone just shows up with what they made and a story about how it went.
      </p>
      <p>
        We started in 2025 with a small group and a simple idea: actually cook from the cookbooks sitting on your shelf, and find a table to bring it to. A year later, events sell out within hours and we've cooked our way through cuisines from around the world — Greek, Moroccan, Caribbean, Vietnamese, and more.
      </p>
      <h2 id="how-it-works">How it works</h2>
      <p>
        Each month we pick a cookbook. Everyone chooses a recipe, cooks it at home, and brings it to share at our gathering in Toronto. The result is a table full of dishes from the same book, interpreted differently by everyone who cooked from it. It's part potluck, part book club, and entirely about the food.
      </p>
      <h2 id="the-details">The details</h2>
      <p>
        Events are free to attend — the only cost is the groceries for your dish. We meet monthly at Jrew's (165 Niagara St, Toronto), with capacity for 35 people. Early access to RSVPs goes to our newsletter subscribers and WhatsApp community first.
      </p>
      <h2 id="join-us">Join us</h2>
      <p>
        Subscribe to our newsletter for early access to upcoming events, or follow us on Instagram to see what past nights looked like. If you have a cookbook you'd love to cook from as a group, reply to any newsletter and let us know.
      </p>
    </div>
    <section class="mt-12 border-t border-border pt-10">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl font-semibold">Your hosts</h2>
      <div class="mt-6 grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2">
        {
          authors.map((author) => (
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <img src={author.avatar} alt="" width="48" height="48" class="h-12 w-12 rounded-full" />
              <div>
                <div class="font-serif text-base font-semibold">{author.name}</div>
                <div class="mt-1 text-sm text-muted-foreground">{author.bio}</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          ))
        }
      </div>
    </section>
    <section class="mt-12 border-t border-border pt-10">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl font-semibold">Find us</h2>
      <div class="mt-4 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
        <a href="https://lu.ma/sautesundaysto" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full bg-foreground px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-semibold text-background hover:opacity-90 transition-opacity">
          RSVP on Luma
        </a>
        <a href="https://www.instagram.com/sautesundays.to/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full border border-border px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-semibold hover:bg-muted transition-colors">
          Instagram
        </a>
        <a href="https://chat.whatsapp.com/GmxcTL5eYwsKqwb23VBjJL" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full border border-border px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-semibold hover:bg-muted transition-colors">
          WhatsApp Community
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>